commitResults.messageBody:
Add RemoveStudentCommand and RemoveStudentCommandParser to facilitate
removing student.

How it works: The user's input to remove a student will be parsed by the
RemoveStudentCommandParser to obtain the student's name and its class.
The Parser returns a RemoveStudentCommand that removes the student from the
class upon execution.

Refractored Person.java to Student.java, some functions related to
Person also renamed to Student. Will continue to rename as time goes on
as there is too much to remove at one go without risking breakage of
code.

TempClass.java is put in place as a stub until code is merged with
actual implementation of Class object.

commitResults.messageBody:
RemoveStudentCommandParser looks for Index of Student in a Class to
remove the Student from that Class.

Class now has UniqueStudentList to represent the List of Student that
are in the Class.

Amended some test cases after refactoring Person to Student.

Amended or removed some test cases after changing the signature of
Student constructor, the number of parameters are significantly reduced.
The constructor now only requires Name.

Temporarily created a UniqueStudentList stub for class "classStub" upon
running the application. This allows for testing of
RemoveStudentCommand - try `remove /s 1 /c classStub` repeatedly, you
should see different Student being removed each time. This should be
removed after addStudentCommand is implemented to directly add student
into a UniqueStudentList of a Class.
